.TH MWB 1 "2026-06-21" "mwb-linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mwb \- Linux client compatible with PowerToys Mouse Without Borders
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mwb
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mwb
connects a Linux desktop to a Windows machine running Microsoft PowerToys
Mouse Without Borders. It can receive mouse, keyboard, and clipboard events
from Windows, and in bidirectional mode it can forward Linux mouse and keyboard
input back to Windows.
.PP
Bidirectional input currently depends on X11 tools for edge detection and
device isolation. Receive-only operation can work without those X11 controls.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-bidi
Enable bidirectional input forwarding from Linux to Windows.
.TP
.BI \-config " path"
Read configuration from
.IR path .
The default is
.IR ~/.config/mwb/config.toml .
.TP
.B \-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BI \-edge " left|right"
Set the local screen edge used to switch to the remote machine. This overrides
the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-no-clipboard
Disable clipboard sharing. This overrides the configuration file.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is TOML. Required fields are:
.TP
.B host
IP address or hostname of the Windows machine.
.TP
.B key
Security key from PowerToys Mouse Without Borders.
.TP
.B name
Display name for the Linux machine.
.PP
Optional fields include
.BR port ,
.BR remote_width ,
.BR remote_height ,
.BR edge ,
.BR clipboard ,
.BR accel_multiplier ,
and
.BR inbound_multiplier .
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
mwb -bidi -edge left
mwb -config ~/.config/mwb/config.toml
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/mwb/config.toml
Default per-user configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/user/mwb.service
Systemd user service installed by the Debian package.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xinput (1),
.BR xdotool (1),
.BR xclip (1)
